The paper deals with the problem of communication capacity in an asynchronous point-to-point communication system without feedback, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance of training-based schemes, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.MM). The system model and decoder operation involve control systems (cs.SY).
